The paper discusses the use of virtualized and cloud architectures for 5G networks, which are primarily related to networking and information theory (cs.NI, cs.IT). The paper also focuses on joint interference management and network provisioning, which involves system-level optimization and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of signal processing algorithms for interference management, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
